00:02:13.099 --> 00:02:18.090
Pollinate, of course, means to fertilize,
so it’s pretty easy to understand what the

00:02:18.090 --> 00:02:20.659
catcalling bug was getting at here.

00:02:20.659 --> 00:02:23.060
The Santa Clause
Disney has made a lot of Christmas movies

00:02:23.060 --> 00:02:25.519
over the years and one of the best ones has
to be 1994’s The Santa Clause.

00:02:25.519 --> 00:02:26.519
Near the start of the movie, Charlie is watching
his dad fly off the roof and remarks, “You’re

00:02:26.519 --> 00:02:27.519
flying!”

00:02:27.519 --> 00:02:32.459
Without missing a beat, Tim Allen’s Santa
responds that he is used to flying as he lived

00:02:32.459 --> 00:02:33.459
through the sixties.

00:02:33.459 --> 00:02:37.069
This is clearly a reference to the drug filled
decade that was the 60’s and it is definitely

00:02:37.069 --> 00:02:39.310
a joke that most kids would have totally missed.

00:02:39.310 --> 00:02:43.120
We’re guessing that more than a few parents,
who may or may not have been flying themselves

00:02:43.120 --> 00:02:45.769
in the sixties, enjoyed this sneaky joke!

00:02:45.769 --> 00:02:49.439
The Emperors New Groove
Kronk is probably the best part of The Emperor’s

00:02:49.439 --> 00:02:52.689
New Groove so it only makes sense that he
was at the center of the film’s most cleverly

00:02:52.689 --> 00:02:54.499
placed adult joke.

00:02:54.499 --> 00:02:59.459
When we see Kronk out camping in a tent that
was so small, it’s easy to just brush this

00:02:59.459 --> 00:03:01.029
off as a joke about his size.

00:03:01.029 --> 00:03:05.200
But, once you realize that the tent is strategically
placed over his crotch, it becomes pretty

00:03:05.200 --> 00:03:09.749
clear that Disney is playing off the idea
of men “pitching a tent” in bed.

00:03:09.749 --> 00:03:13.340
This is one of the studios cleverest mature
moments and we have to give them full points

00:03:13.340 --> 00:03:15.150
for execution!

00:03:15.150 --> 00:03:17.760
Cars 2
